sentences: Gene J. Bertoncini (born 6 April 1937) is an American jazz guitarist.
His father, Mario Bertoncini (1901–1978), played guitar and harmonica.
He graduated from high school and attended the University of Notre Dame, where, in 1959, he earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Architectural Engineering.

He was part of the staff orchestras on shows featuring Merv Griffin and Jack Paar, and most famously The Tonight Show Starring Johnny Carson.
For some eighteen years, Bertoncini played Sunday and Monday evenings at the Bistro La Madeleine on West 43rd Street in New York City.
Currently Bertoncini is on the faculty of William Paterson University in Wayne, New Jersey.
